title: (x) United Way logo - custom designed {Franz}
content:
![](http://web.archive.org/web/20080706110258im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/messages/83/40829.jpg)   
   
Any clues what this font is called?

 [‹ (x) eu icat - Reykjavik Two {Tom C}](http://web.archive.org/web/20080706110258/http:/www.typophile.com/node/5669 "Go to previous forum topic") [(x) Daddy Yankee logo - calligraphy by Mark Allen {Valentine (self)} ›](http://web.archive.org/web/20080706110258/http:/www.typophile.com/node/5658 "Go to next forum topic")
author: anonymous

comments.content:
Hmmm... I'd say ITC Officina Serif or TheSerif Condensed style.   
Shame about the poor res. Don't know what it is (yet).

I don't think either of those is right, because the serifs (of W for instance) aren't the same as those fonts.   
   
Still looking too.

This is a custom job by [FutureBrand](http://web.archive.org/web/20080706110258/http:/www.futurebrand.com/), I don't think there even is a font. Here's a [high-res image](http://web.archive.org/web/20080706110258/http:/www.unitedwayla.org/pages/camp_ctr/logos_matierals/uw_4p_ful.jpg) of the whole logo.

Found [this](http://web.archive.org/web/20080706110258/http:/www.underconsideration.com/mt-static/mt-comments.cgi?entry_id=1956) on [Speak Up](http://web.archive.org/web/20080706110258/http:/www.underconsideration.com/speakup/), by the designer:

> * * *
> **quote:**
> 
> "as noted before, it looks like Officina Sans."   
> Definitely similarities and we did reference a few typefaces while crafting this. Lets call it Weinberger Bold.
> 
> * * *

Wow, Franz! Your research is awesome and much appreciated!! ![:-)](http://web.archive.org/web/20080706110258im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/clipart/happy.gif)   
   
Joseph
